Description: Ostracon, large fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery vessel, the fabric is grey in section and contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a light-brown slip and faint traces of two lines of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393975) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393975)
